This was our first time ordering from them and the food was awful. The fries weren’t cooked and they arrived extra soggy. They need to work on packaging for delivery so fries can arrive less soggy or deliver separate in a paper bag. The toast on the sandwich was burnt ($15 white bread- you’d think if it burns the cost is covered to replace the toast!) The milkshake tasted like a water down slushie. The chicken was so salty it wasn’t edible. The opportunity to elevate service is now. Because we are paying inflation on food and delivery I’d expect when ordering $80 from a diner it would at least be a decent meal.

I ordered from them via postmates and ran into a couple of problems with them. 1. A whole portion of my order was missing and when I called them, the very rude woman that picked up the phone insisted she put it. Why would I call if you put all my order there? 2. The food was lukewarm, dry, and the broiled chicken was overly salty. 3. They cancelled my order, and when I reordered and changed it slightly, they gave me the first order. Why cancel it in the first place then? All in all, I should've just saved my money. I am never ordering from here again.

Our waiter (Jonathan) was so kind and accommodating. Food was delicious- eggs benedict and fruit salad for the win! Clean, friendly, excellent service. Will definitely be back.

Park Slope is blessed with at least a half dozen good diners, but this one stands out for a few reasons. Unlike others, it feels cozy (lots of booths!) and "period" without trying too hard; the menu is full of good Mexican interpolations (I had huevos rancheros and a cuppa); and it's spotless inside.

Two stars only for the food. Choices and breakfast menu are pretty good particularly the Mexican fare. What was more than disappointing was the service. The first time we went the food was great and the service was lousy. The second time we went the food was still great, the service was even worse - unfortunately the same waiter. - I don't understand you work for tips at least fake interest in the customer. I usually tip well over 20% especially for breakfast. The waiter took forever to take our order (it was not busy). Then copped an attitude when my wife ask to have the ranchero sauce on the side. Never came back for coffee or water..we finally had to get up and ask. - Why bother...too many good bagel or breakfast places on 7th Ave or 9th street to deal with "you're bothering me attitude".

THEY TRIED TO STEAL MY PHONE. If I could give them less than 1 star I would. I went there for brunch with friends. Upon leaving I soon realized I no longer had my phone. I retraced my steps back to the diner and asked the staff if I happened to leave my phone on the table after I left. All the staff denied having seen my phone so I went outside and used GPS to track my phone. GPS said my phone was at the restaurant so once again I went in to ask if someone had found my phone, again they "looked" and tried to convince me I left it at home. After about 5-10 minutes of denial i proceeded to tell them I had a GPS tracker on it and was going to set off the alarm, then and only then did they go (without hesitation)to the box where they stored the menus and pulled out my phone. Mind you I still.had my phone when they took up the menus. They tried to steal my phone, thank God for my GPS tracker.

I was harassed by my delivery driver from this restaurant and I will never order from here again. I ordered through the Seamless app and left a standard tip. When my driver arrived, he harassed me on my doorstep, repeatedly claiming that the standard tip I had given him was too low. He continued badgering me for over a minute until I finally just shut the door and he walked away. Extremely inappropriate for an adult man to be at a woman's doorstep behaving in this manner while on the job, not only was it unprofessional but I also felt unsafe.
